result.adr_address: 11 Stanley St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Sanka Teppanyaki

reviews.text: My new favorite teppanyaki spot in Hong Kong! Service was impeccable and the the decor was modern and tasteful. The food is the true star, it was presented in a timely manner without all the distracting flair of other establishments.

One of the best teppanyakis I’ve ever had. I suggest trying the multiple course menus so you can get a taste of almost all the dishes.
The environment is cozy and nice.
I also like the dessert a lit. It was a good ending to a big meal!

I have been to this restaurant many times the best chef and food but the worst services always  ! Today I call to make reservation for a private room they told me  the only room available can hold 6 ppl so instead of 8 we decided to limit our group to 6 to accommodate . After all the fuss the girl who answered the phone said the chef  can only cook for us at 6 pm or 9 pm not at 730 pm the time I am that at I requested ...what the hell ! She should had said  something up front ! So is not whether their room can hold 6 or if they actually have a room but there is no chef ??? Who normally will dine at 6 pm and so the chef need to go at 730 ?? Ridiculous for someone who charge $1900 per head !!!
Nice Japanese seafood
Teppanyaki with perfection. Very harmonious fusion of Japanese and French cuisine.
